0", "committee": "HED", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2018/hed23.mp3", "start_seconds": 146.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2018-02-14T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HED", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2018/hed23.mp3", "start_seconds": 146.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2018-02-14T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HED", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2018/hed23.mp3", "start_seconds": 146.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2018-02-27T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HOU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2018/hou30.mp3", "start_seconds": 3106.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2018-02-27T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HOU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2018/hou30.mp3", "start_seconds": 3106.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2018-02-27T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HOU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2018/hou30.mp3", "start_seconds": 3106.0}, {"meeting_datetime": "2018-02-27T00:00:00-06:00", "committee": "HOU", "url": "https://sdpb.sd.gov/sdpbpodcast/2018/hou30.mp3", "start_seconds": 3106.0}], "bill_versions": [{"bill_id": 8869, "bill_version_id": 46785, "bill_version": "Introduced", "bill_version_date": "2018-01-04T15:11:23.377-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to require school districts to adopt a policy limiting the use of restraint and seclusion. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 13-32 be amended by adding a NEW SECTION to read: The school board of each school district shall adopt or revise a school district policy on the use of restraint and seclusion. The policy shall contain the following provisions: (1) A procedure for immediately notifying the parent or guardian of the student, unless the student is emancipated, of an incident requiring the use of restraint or seclusion; (2) A prohibition on the use of prone restraint, defined as physical pressure applied to any part of the student's body to keep the student in a face down position on the floor or other surface; (3) A prohibition on the use of involuntary confinement of a student locked alone in a room; and (4) Training on crisis prevention and the proper use of restraint and seclusion. 100 copies were printed on recycled paper by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.167 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from existing statutes are indicated by overstrikes."}, {"bill_id": 8869, "bill_version_id": 48010, "bill_version": "Senate Education Engrossed", "bill_version_date": "2018-01-25T12:57:20.63-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to require school districts to adopt a policy limiting the use of restraint and seclusion. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 13-32 be amended by adding a NEW SECTION to read: The school board of each school district shall adopt or revise a school district policy for school district employees on the use of restraint and seclusion. The policy shall contain the following provisions: (1) A procedure for notifying the parent or guardian of the student on the same business day, unless the student is emancipated, of an incident requiring the use of restraint or seclusion; (2) A prohibition on the use of prone restraint, defined as physical pressure applied to any part of the student's body to keep the student in a face down position on the floor or other surface; (3) A prohibition on the use of involuntary confinement of a student locked alone in a room; and (4) Training on crisis prevention and the proper use of restraint and seclusion."}, {"bill_id": 8869, "bill_version_id": 49241, "bill_version": "House Education Engrossed", "bill_version_date": "2018-02-14T10:50:40.13-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to require school districts to adopt a policy limiting the use of restraint and seclusion. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 13-32 be amended by adding a NEW SECTION to read: The school board of each school district shall adopt or revise a school district policy for school district employees on the use of restraint and seclusion. The policy shall contain the following provisions: (1) A procedure for immediately notifying the parent or guardian of the student, unless the student is emancipated, of an incident requiring the use of restraint or seclusion; (2) A prohibition on the use of prone restraint, defined as physical pressure applied to any part of the student's body to keep the student in a face down position on the floor or other surface; and (3) A prohibition on the use of involuntary confinement of a student locked alone in a room. 100 copies were printed on recycled paper by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.167 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from existing statutes are indicated by overstrikes."}, {"bill_id": 8869, "bill_version_id": 50505, "bill_version": "Conference Committee Engrossed", "bill_version_date": "2018-03-08T16:15:12.303-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to require school districts to adopt a policy limiting the use of restraint and seclusion. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 13-32 be amended by adding a NEW SECTION to read: The school board of each school district shall adopt or revise a school district policy for school district employees on the use of restraint and seclusion. The policy shall contain the following provisions: (1) A procedure for notifying the parent or guardian of the student, unless the student is emancipated, of an incident requiring the use of restraint or seclusion; (2) A prohibition on the use of prone restraint, defined as physical pressure applied to any part of the student's body to keep the student in a face down position on the floor or other surface, except when the use is necessary and reasonable in manner and moderate in degree; and (3) A prohibition on the use of involuntary confinement of a student locked alone in a room, unless there is a clear and present danger. 100 copies were printed on recycled paper by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.167 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from existing statutes are indicated by overstrikes."}, {"bill_id": 8869, "bill_version_id": 50499, "bill_version": "Enrolled", "bill_version_date": "2018-03-08T16:17:26.293-06:00", "bill_text": ""}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 8869, "action_date": "2018-01-09T12:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 46890, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/46890.pdf", "status_text": "First read in Senate and referred to", "journal_page": 21, "committee_id_action": 395, "committee_id_assigned": 370, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 8869, "action_date": "2018-01-23T07:45:00-06:00", "document_id": 47396, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/47396.pdf", "status_text": "Scheduled for hearing", "journal_page": 0, "committee_id_action": 370, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 8869, "action_date": "2018-01-25T07:45:00-06:00", "document_id": 47619, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/47619.pdf", "status_text": "Scheduled for hearing", "journal_page": 0, "committee_id_action": 370, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 8869, "action_date": "2018-01-25T07:45:00-06:00", "document_id": 47984, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/47984.pdf", "status_text": "Motion to amend", "journal_page": 0, "committee_id_action": 370, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "P", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 8869, "action_date": "2018-01-25T07:45:00-06:00", "document_id": 47984, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/47984.pdf", "status_te